Acrobatic (Mythic)			KEY:Acrobatic						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Acrobatic																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your grace and fluidity are beyond compare.																																																																																									BONUS:SKILL|Acrobatics|2	BONUS:SKILL|Fly|2																																																										BENEFIT:The bonus on Acrobatics and Fly skill checks from Acrobatic increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat an Acrobatics or Fly check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Acrobatic.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Acrobatic	SOURCEPAGE:p.54
Alertness (Mythic)			KEY:Alertness						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Alertness																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your powers of perception surpass everyone's, whether used to observe your surroundings or the intentions of others.																																																																																						BONUS:SKILL|Perception|2	BONUS:SKILL|Sense Motive|2																																																								BENEFIT:The bonus on Perception and Sense Motive skill checks from Alertness increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat a Perception or Sense Motive check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Alertness.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Alertness	SOURCEPAGE:p.54
Alignment Channel (Mythic)		KEY:Alignment Channel					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Alignment Channel																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:The power of your faith harms all creatures that follow the alignment you abhor.																																																																																																																																																																BENEFIT:Your channeled energy affects any creatures with the alignment chosen when you took Alignment Channel (not just outsiders, and not just those with the alignment subtype), but grants only half healing or deals only half damage to these targets. Alternatively, you can expend two uses of mythic power when using Alignment Channel to affect all targets of the chosen alignment as if they had that alignment subtype.	INFO:Prerequisite|Alignment Channel.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Alignment Channel	SOURCEPAGE:p.54
Animal Affinity (Mythic)		KEY:Animal Affinity					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Animal Affinity																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You have a greater affinity with wild animals, and can speak with them.																																																																																											BONUS:SKILL|Handle Animal|2	BONUS:SKILL|Ride|2																																																									BENEFIT:The bonus on Handle Animal and Ride skill checks from Animal Affinity increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to speak with animals as the spell. Your caster level for this effect is %1.|MythicLevel*2	INFO:Prerequisite|Animal Affinity.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Animal Affinity	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Arcane Armor Training (Mythic)	KEY:Arcane Armor Training				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Arcane Armor Training																										PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You've adapted your spellcasting to overcome limitations of wearing armor.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:You don't have to spend a swift action to gain the reduction to arcane spell failure chance from Arcane Armor Training. Furthermore, if you're wearing light armor, reduce your arcane spell failure chance by 20%%.	INFO:Prerequisite|Arcane Armor Training.																																																																																																								BONUS:EQMARMOR|SPELLFAILURE|-20|TYPE=ARMORFAILURE	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Arcane Armor Training	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Arcane Blast (Mythic)			KEY:Arcane Blast					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Arcane Blast																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can manipulate raw eldritch energies to do more than just deal damage.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:When you use Arcane Blast, you may halve the damage dice to also perform your choice of either a trip or bull rush combat maneuver against the target of the blast. You can't move with an opponent you bull rush with this feat. You gain a bonus on your combat maneuver check for this attempt equal to half the spell level of the spell you sacrificed when using Arcane Blast, and you can substitute your Intelligence or Charisma modifier in place of your Strength modifier when determining your combat maneuver bonus.&nl;In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to change the damage dice of your Arcane Blast to d8s instead of d6s.	INFO:Prerequisite|Arcane Blast.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Arcane Blast	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Arcane Shield (Mythic)			KEY:Arcane Shield					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Arcane Shield																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You sculpt spells into a powerful, enduring arcane barriers.																																																																																																																																																											BENEFIT:You %1 to the deflection bonus granted to your AC when you use your Arcane Shield. You can expend one use of mythic power when using this feat to extend the duration to %2 rounds.|MythicLevel/2|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Arcane Shield.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Arcane Shield	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Arcane Strike (Mythic)			KEY:Arcane Strike					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Arcane Strike																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Using your amazing arcane talents, you can deliver devastating blows infused with magical energy.																																																																																																																																																															BENEFIT:Whenever you use Arcane Strike to enhance your weapons, the effect lasts for 1 minute instead of 1 round. If you expend one use of mythic power when using Arcane Strike, you can also add any one magic weapon special ability with a base price modifier of +%1 to your weapons.|Feat_MythicArcaneStrike_Bonus	INFO:Prerequisite|Arcane Strike.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Arcane Strike	DEFINE:Feat_MythicArcaneStrike_Bonus|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_MythicArcaneStrike_Bonus|floor((MythicTierLevel+2)/3)	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Aspect of the Beast (Mythic)		KEY:Aspect of the Beast				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Aspect of the Beast																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your blood burns with savage fury, giving you bestial powers and abilities.																																			BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Mythic Aspect of the Beast Selection|1																																																																																																																											BENEFIT:Your bestial nature manifests itself in one of the following ways. You choose the manifestation when you choose the feat, and you can't change it.	BENEFIT:&nl;Mythic Senses (Ex): If you have normal vision, you gain darkvision 30 feet. If you have low-light vision, you gain darkvision 60 feet. If you have darkvision, the range of your darkvision increases by 30 feet plus 10 feet per tier.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Mythic Aspect of the Beast ~ Mythic Senses	BENEFIT:&nl;Mythic Claws (Ex): You grow a pair of powerful claws. These claws are primary attacks that deal 1d4 points of damage (1d3 if you're Small). If you already have claws, the damage they deal increases by one die type (d4s become d6s, d3s become d4s, and so on). You can expend one use of mythic power when you hit with both claws during the same round to rend with those claws, dealing extra damage equal to one claw's damage plus 1-1/2 times your Strength bonus.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Mythic Aspect of the Beast ~ Mythic Claws	BENEFIT:&nl;Mythic Leap (Ex): You can make a running jump without needing to run 10 feet beforehand. In addition, you gain a +5 bonus on your Acrobatics checks to determine the success of that jump and the distance covered. If you already have the predator's leap manifestation of Aspect of the Beast, the bonus on your Acrobatics checks increases to +10.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Mythic Aspect of the Beast ~ Mythic Leap	BENEFIT:&nl;Mythic Instinct (Ex): You gain a +2 bonus on initiative checks and a +2 bonus on Survival checks. These bonuses stack with those gained from the wild instinct manifestation of Aspect of the Beast.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Mythic Aspect of the Beast ~ Mythic Instinct	INFO:Prerequisite|Aspect of the Beast.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Aspect of the Beast	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Athletic (Mythic)				KEY:Athletic						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Athletic																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You excel far beyond others at acts of physical prowess.																																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|Climb|2	BONUS:SKILL|Swim|2																																																										BENEFIT:The bonus on Climb and Swim skill checks from Athletic increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat a Climb or Swim check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Athletic.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Athletic	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Augment Summoning (Mythic)		KEY:Augment Summoning					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Augment Summoning																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your summoning spells bring not mere ordinary beasts, but instead mythic creatures.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:Any creature you summon using a summon spell is considered mythic for the purpose of interacting with other mythic creatures. It doesn't gain any mythic abilities or power, but is affected by mythic spells and abilities as if it were a 1st-tier mythic creature. Additionally, if the creature summoned has damage reduction, its damage reduction becomes DR/epic.	INFO:Prerequisite|Augment Summoning.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Augment Summoning	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Bleeding Critical (Mythic)		KEY:Bleeding Critical					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Bleeding Critical	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Mythic Feat,Critical Focus																						PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your deadliest blows unleash rivers of blood.																																																																																																																																																																				BENEFIT:The bleed damage dealt with Bleeding Critical increases by %1. Stopping this bleed damage requires a Heal check with a DC equal to %2. Any magical healing ends the bleed damage normally.&nl;You can expend one use of mythic power to deal 1 Con bleed, in addition to the hit point bleed damage you deal with this feat. This effect increases by 1 for each additional use of mythic power you expend.|MythicLevel|15+HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Bleeding Critical, Critical Focus (mythic).	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Bleeding Critical	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Blind-Fight (Mythic)			KEY:Blind Fight						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Blind Fight																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:No creature can avoid your preternatural senses.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to ignore all miss chances due to concealment or total concealment for %1 rounds.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Blind-Fight.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Blind Fight	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Catch Off-Guard (Mythic)		KEY:Catch Off-Guard					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Catch Off-Guard																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:In your hands, anything is a deadly weapon.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:The damage dealt when you use improvised weapons increases by %1. You also gain a +%1 bonus to CMD when an opponent attempts to sunder or disarm an improvised weapon you're wielding.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Catch Off-Guard.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Catch Off-Guard	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Channel Smite (Mythic)			KEY:Channel Smite					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Channel Smite																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your weapon a conduit of divine energy.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:When using Channel Smite, you gain a bonus on your attack roll equal to the number of d6s granted by your channel energy class feature. This is either a sacred bonus (if channeling positive energy) or a profane bonus (if channeling negative energy). If your attack misses the target, you can expend one use of mythic power as a free action to release the channeled energy, producing the normal effects of your channel energy class feature centered on the creature you were attempting to smite.	INFO:Prerequisite|Channel Smite.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Channel Smite	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Charge Through (Mythic)			KEY:Charge Through					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Charge Through																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can plow through those who stand between you and the target of your charge.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:When charging, you can ignore allies in your path when determining whether or not you can charge your target. Furthermore, after you have attempted at least one overrun with Charge Through, you can expend one use of mythic power as a free action to attempt another overrun against a different opponent in the path of the same charge.	INFO:Prerequisite|Charge Through.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Charge Through	SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Cleave (Mythic)				KEY:Cleave						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Cleave																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can cleave any foe within your reach.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:Whenever you use Cleave or Great Cleave, one of your attacks can be made against a foe that is within your reach, but not adjacent to the foe you attacked. You can expend one use of mythic power when you use Cleave or Great Cleave to continue making attacks against foes within your reach, regardless of their position, as long as you continue to hit each foe. You can't use this ability to attack a foe more than once per round.	INFO:Prerequisite|Cleave.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Cleave	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Combat Expertise (Mythic)		KEY:Combat Expertise					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can dart out of the way of attacks with skill and defiance.																																																																																																														BONUS:VAR|CombatExpertiseModifierAC|2																																					BENEFIT:Whenever you use Combat Expertise, you gain an additional +2 dodge bonus to your Armor Class. You can expend one use of mythic power to negate the penalties on melee attack rolls and combat maneuver checks caused by using Combat Expertise for 1 minute.	INFO:Prerequisite|Combat Expertise.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Combat Expertise	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Combat Reflexes (Mythic)		KEY:Combat Reflexes					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Reflexes																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You strike viciously whenever your foe gives you an opening.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:You can make any number of additional attacks of opportunity per round. As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to, until the start of your next turn, make attacks of opportunity against foes you've already made attacks of opportunity against this round if they provoke attacks of opportunity from you by moving.	INFO:Prerequisite|Combat Reflexes.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Combat Reflexes	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Command Undead (Mythic)			KEY:Command Undead					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Command Undead																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your control of the undead is nearly absolute.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:When you command undead, the DC of the Will save increases by %1, and intelligent undead get no additional saves beyond their first to resist your commands. Any attempts by non-mythic creatures to control undead you command automatically fail, and you gain a +4 bonus on Charisma checks to prevent mythic creatures from stealing control of your undead.|MythicLevel/2	INFO:Prerequisite|Command Undead.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Command Undead	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Critical Focus (Mythic)			KEY:Critical Focus					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Critical Focus																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your blows unerringly find your target's vital spots.																																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:You automatically confirm critical threats against non-mythic opponents. In addition, when you threaten a critical hit against a creature wearing armor with the fortification special ability or similar effect, that creature must roll twice and take the worse result when determining critical hit negation.	INFO:Prerequisite|Critical Focus.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Critical Focus	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Critical Mastery (Mythic)		KEY:Critical Mastery					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Critical Mastery	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Mythic Feat,Critical Focus																						PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your critical hits are versatile and devastating.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:When using Critical Mastery, increase the number of critical feats you may apply by %1.|max(1,floor(MythicLevel/3))	INFO:Prerequisite|Critical Focus (mythic), Critical Mastery.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Critical Mastery	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Dastardly Finish (Mythic)		KEY:Dastardly Finish					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dastardly Finish																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You strike downed, dazed, and staggered opponents with deadly efficiency.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:You can deliver a coup de grace to dazed and staggered non-mythic opponents. In addition, when any creature makes a Fortitude saving throw to survive one of your coup de grace attempts, it takes a -%1 penalty to that saving throw.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Dastardly Finish.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Dastardly Finish	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Dazzling Display (Mythic)		KEY:Dazzling Display					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dazzling Display																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can quickly deter others with your martial mastery.																																																																																																																																																																		BENEFIT:While wielding the weapon with which you have Weapon Focus, you can use Dazzling Display as a standard action with a -5 penalty on your Intimidate check, as a move action with a -10 penalty, or as a swift action with a -20 penalty. You can expend one use of mythic power when you make a Dazzling Display to make those affected by the display frightened rather than shaken.	INFO:Prerequisite|Dazzling Display.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Dazzling Display	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Deadly Aim (Mythic)			KEY:Deadly Aim						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deadly Aim																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your aim is truly devastating.																																																																																																																																																																											BENEFIT:When you use Deadly Aim, you gain a +3 bonus on ranged damage rolls instead of +2. When your base attack bonus reaches +4, and every +4 thereafter, the bonus on ranged damage rolls increases by +3 rather than +2.	INFO:Prerequisite|Deadly Aim.																																																																													TEMPBONUS:EQ|Weapon,Ranged|WEAPON|DAMAGE|-1*2*DeadlyAimModifier|TYPE=Temporary	TEMPBONUS:EQ|Weapon,Ranged|WEAPON|DAMAGE|3*DeadlyAimModifier|TYPE=Temporary	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Deadly Aim	SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Deadly Stroke (Mythic)			KEY:Deadly Stroke					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deadly Stroke																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can kill with a single stroke.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:When making a Deadly Stroke attack, you can expend one use of mythic power to instantly kill a non-mythic living creature. A Fortitude save (DC %1) negates this effect, though the attack still deals double damage and Con bleed as Deadly Stroke. Constructs, oozes, and creatures immune to critical hits or precision-based damage can't be killed with this feat.|10+BAB+MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Deadly Stroke.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Deadly Stroke	SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Death from Above (Mythic)		KEY:Death from Above					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Death from Above																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:When attacking from the air or higher ground, you bear down on your enemy to deadly effect.																																																																																																																																																																BENEFIT:Whenever you charge an opponent from higher ground, or from above while flying, the critical multiplier of your weapon increases by 2 (to a maximum of x6). This doesn't stack with other abilities that increase a weapon's critical multiplier. If your charge attack hits, you can perform a trip combat maneuver against the attack's target as a free action without provoking attacks of opportunity.	INFO:Prerequisite|Death from Above.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Death from Above	SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Deceitful (Mythic)			KEY:Deceitful						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deceitful																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your power to mislead is beyond compare.																																																																																									BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|2	BONUS:SKILL|Disguise|2																																																										BENEFIT:The bonus on Bluff and Disguise skill checks from Deceitful increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat a Bluff or Disguise check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Deceitful.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Deceitful	SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Deepsight (Mythic)			KEY:Deepsight						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deepsight																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your sharp eyes can penetrate deeper into the darkness, revealing more to you.																																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|DarkvisionRange|10*MythicLevel																													BENEFIT:The range of your darkvision increases by 10 feet per tier.	INFO:Prerequisite|Deepsight.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Deepsight	SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Defensive Combat Training (Mythic)	KEY:Defensive Combat Training			CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Defensive Combat Training																										PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,4																																				DESC:Your defensive capabilities in combat are unmatched.																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|CMD|HalfMythicLevel																																															BENEFIT:Add +%1 to your CMD.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Defensive Combat Training, 4th mythic tier.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Defensive Combat Training	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Deflect Arrows (Mythic)			KEY:Deflect Arrows					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deflect Arrows																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You deflect projectiles and ray spells with uncanny skill.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:When using Deflect Arrows, you can deflect %1 additional ranged attacks per round. You can expend one use of mythic power as an immediate action to deflect a single ray from a ray spell or effect targeting you.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Deflect Arrows.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Deflect Arrows	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Deft Hands (Mythic)			KEY:Deft Hand						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deft Hand																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your hands are astonishingly nimble.																																																																																						BONUS:SKILL|Disable Device|2	BONUS:SKILL|Sleight of Hand|2																																																								BENEFIT:The bonus on Disable Device and Sleight of Hand skill checks from Deft Hands increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat a Disable Device or Sleight of Hand check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Deft Hands.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Deft Hand	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Detect Expertise (Mythic)		KEY:Detect Expertise					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Detect Expertise																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can sense a creature's magical abilities with just a mere glance.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:You gain the benefit of Detect Expertise immediately (without needing to observe a creature for 3 rounds) when using the divinations listed in Detect Expertise. Non-mythic creatures cannot attempt a Will save to resist this effect.	INFO:Prerequisite|Detect Expertise.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Detect Expertise	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Disruptive (Mythic)			KEY:Disruptive						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Disruptive																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're a master at disrupting nearby spellcasters.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:The DC to cast spells defensively within your threatened area increases by %1. This stacks with the increase granted by Disruptive. In addition, even if you can't make attacks of opportunity, non-mythic spellcasters are still wary of you and continue to suffer from the effects of Disruptive.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Disruptive.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Disruptive	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Distance Thrower (Mythic)		KEY:Distance Thrower					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Distance Thrower																					PRESTAT:1,STR=17				PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:There's virtually no limit to your powerful throwing arm.																																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:Thrown weapons wielded by you have twice their normal range.	INFO:Prerequisite|Str 17, Distance Thrower.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Distance Thrower	BONUS:RANGEMULT|THROWN|100	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Divine Interference (Mythic)		KEY:Divine Interference				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Divine Interference																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your divine power thwarts enemies of your faith.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:When you use Divine Interference, the penalty on your opponent's attack roll is equal to twice the level of the spell sacrificed. You can expend one use of mythic power when you sacrifice the spell to increase the penalty to triple the level of the spell sacrificed.	INFO:Prerequisite|Divine Interference.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Divine Interference	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Dodge (Mythic)				KEY:Dodge							CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:When focused, you become nearly impossible to strike.																																									BONUS:COMBAT|AC|1|TYPE=Dodge.STACK																																																																																																													BENEFIT:The bonus to AC from Dodge increases by 1. As an immediate action, you can expend one use of mythic power to grant yourself an additional +10 dodge bonus to AC against one attack.	INFO:Prerequisite|Dodge.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Dodge	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Dreadful Carnage (Mythic)		KEY:Dreadful Carnage					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dreadful Carnage																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your kills are truly frightening to behold.																																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:When you use Dreadful Carnage, you affect non-mythic enemies within 60 feet in addition to all enemies within 30 feet. You can expend one use of mythic power before making the Intimidate check to cause enemies demoralized by Dreadful Carnage to become frightened instead of shaken, for the same duration as the normal shaken effect. While frightened by this ability, an enemy takes a -%1 penalty on attack rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and ability checks.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Dreadful Carnage.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Dreadful Carnage	SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Eagle Eyes (Mythic)			KEY:Eagle Eyes						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Eagle Eyes																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You eyesight rivals that of the most far-seeing raptors.																																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:You ignore up to -10 in penalties due to distance on visual Perception checks, instead of the normal -5. As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to ignore all penalties due to distance on visual Perception checks for 1 round.	INFO:Prerequisite|Eagle Eyes.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Eagle Eyes	SOURCEPAGE:p.64
# Waiting on bloodline rework
Eldritch Heritage (Mythic)		KEY:Eldritch Heritage					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Eldritch Heritage																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:The blood of your sorcerous ancestor mingles with your mythic power to great effect.																																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:You gain sorcerer bloodline powers of the bloodline tied to Eldritch Heritage as if your sorcerer level were your character level - 2. For that bloodline's 1st-level bloodline power, use your full character level to determine its effect; for all other bloodline powers, treat your sorcerer level as your character level - 2.	INFO:Prerequisite|Eldritch Heritage.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Eldritch Heritage	SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Elemental Channel (Mythic)		KEY:Elemental Channel					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Elemental Channel																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your power over elemental beings is nearly absolute.																																																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:Your Elemental Channel can affect any elemental subtype, not just the one you chose when you took Elemental Channel. Each time you use Elemental Channel, you must pick one elemental subtype before using the feat. You can expend one use of mythic power when you use Elemental Channel to choose a second elemental subtype to affect.	INFO:Prerequisite|Elemental Channel.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Elemental Channel	SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Elemental Fist (Mythic)			KEY:Elemental Fist					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Elemental Fist																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your ability to channel elemental power through your unarmed attacks is ferociously potent.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:The extra energy damage dealt by Elemental Fist increases to 1d8 points, and you gain %1 additional uses of Elemental Fist per day. You can expend one use of mythic power as an immediate action to add the extra damage from your Elemental Fist to all of the unarmed strikes you make until the beginning of your next turn. This counts as only one use of Elemental Fist, regardless of the number of attacks that you make in this fashion.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Elemental Fist.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Elemental Fist	BONUS:VAR|ElementalFistUses|MythicLevel	SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Elemental Focus (Mythic)		KEY:Elemental Focus					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Elemental Focus																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your elemental spells are potent and effective.		STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITYSELECTION|Internal|TYPE=MythicElementalFocus	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|%LIST																																																																																																																																		BENEFIT:Choose an energy type in which you already have Elemental Focus. The increase to save DC provided by Elemental Focus and Greater Elemental Focus for spells of the selected energy type is 1 higher. When casting a spell with this energy type's descriptor, you can expend one use of mythic power as part of the casting to force the spell's targets to roll their saving throws twice, taking the lower result.	INFO:Prerequisite|Elemental Focus.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Elemental Focus	SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Elven Accuracy (Mythic)			KEY:Elven Accuracy					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Elven Accuracy																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your elven eyesight cuts though concealment.																																																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:When you make an attack with a longbow or short bow (including composite bows), you can ignore concealment, but not total concealment. You still suffer a miss chance for total concealment, but if you miss due to total concealment, you may reroll your miss chance as per Elven Accuracy.	INFO:Prerequisite|Elven Accuracy.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Elven Accuracy	SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Endurance (Mythic)			KEY:Endurance						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Endurance																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your endurance is truly beyond the pale.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:The bonus on checks and saves from Endurance increases by +%1. You take half the damage when you fail a check to avoid nonlethal damage from a forced march, starvation and thirst, hot or cold environments, or slow suffocation.&nl;You can sleep in heavy armor without becoming fatigued.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Endurance.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Endurance	DEFINE:Feat_Endurance_SaveBonus|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_Endurance_SaveBonus|HalfMythicLevel	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Eschew Materials (Mythic)		KEY:Eschew Materials					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Eschew Materials																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can cast even the most powerful spells without using material components.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:You can cast any spell with a material component costing %1 gp or less without providing that component. If you expend one use of mythic power while casting a spell that requires a material component costing %2 gp or less, you can cast it without providing that component. Expending two uses of mythic power instead allows you to cast a spell that requires a material component costing %3 gp or less without providing that component.|10*MythicLevel|50*MythicLevel|100*MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Eschew Materials.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Eschew Materials	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Far Shot (Mythic)				KEY:Far Shot						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Far Shot																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You make long-ranged attacks with remarkable accuracy.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to ignore all range increment penalties for your ranged attacks until the end of your turn.	INFO:Prerequisite|Far Shot.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Far Shot	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Fast Empathy (Mythic)			KEY:Fast Empathy					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fast Empathy																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can soothe the emotions of wild beasts with nearly supernatural quickness.																																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:You can use wild empathy as a swift action.	INFO:Prerequisite|Fast Empathy.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Fast Empathy	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Fire Music (Mythic)			KEY:Fire Music						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fire Music																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You masterfully weave the ancient melodies of fire into your spells.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:When you use Fire Music to change any of the damage dealt by a bard spell to fire damage, that damage ignores up to %1 fire resistance. If you cast summon monster as a bard spell and choose to give the summoned creature a fiery appearance, increase its fire resistance by 5 (adding to the resistance already granted by Fire Music) and add 1d4 points of fire damage to all of its natural attacks instead of the +1 fire damage normally granted by Fire Music. Creatures with the fire subtype also gain these benefits.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Fire Music.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Fire Music	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Fleet (Mythic)				KEY:Fleet							CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fleet																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're fantastically light on your feet.														STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE																																																																																																																																																BENEFIT:Your base land speed increases by 5 feet, regardless of what armor you wear or whether you're encumbered. This bonus stacks with the bonus gained from Fleet.	INFO:Special|You can take this feat multiple times, but no more than the number of times you've taken non-mythic Fleet. The effects stack.	INFO:Prerequisite|Fleet.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Fleet	PREVARLT:count("ABILITIES","CATEGORY=Mythic Feat","KEY=Fleet"),count("ABILITIES","CATEGORY=FEAT","KEY=Fleet")	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|5	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Furious Focus (Mythic)			KEY:Furious Focus					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Furious Focus																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your attacks create a rhythmic barrage that doesn't sacrifice precision for force.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:When you are using Furious Focus, you don't take Power Attack's penalty on attack rolls that are made as attacks of opportunity. As a free action, you can expend one use of mythic power to negate Power Attack's penalty on all melee attacks you make for 1 round while using this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Furious Focus.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Furious Focus	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Gnome Trickster (Mythic)		KEY:Gnome Trickster					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Gnome Trickster																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1		SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=Feat_GnomeTrickster_Blur_Times|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Blur,12+CHA	SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=Feat_GnomeTrickster_Vanish_Times|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Vanish,11+CHA								DESC:Thanks to your mythic power, the magic in your blood has grown more potent and diverse.																																																																																																																																																																	BENEFIT:You gain the following spell-like abilities: 1/day--blur and vanish.&nl;You can use your gnome spell-like abilities an additional %1 times per day. You can spend these additional uses to use any of your gnome spell-like abilities you wish. Your caster level for your gnome spell-like abilities becomes.|HalfMythicLevel|TL+MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Gnome Trickster.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Gnome Trickster	DEFINE:Feat_GnomeTrickster_Blur_Times|0	DEFINE:Feat_GnomeTrickster_Vanish_Times|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_GnomeTrickster_Blur_Times|1	BONUS:VAR|Feat_GnomeTrickster_Vanish_Times|1	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Gorgon's Fist (Mythic)			KEY:Gorgon's Fist					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Gorgon's Fist																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your strikes debilitate and disorient your foes.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:When you hit a creature while using Gorgon's Fist, if the target fails its Fortitude saving throw, it is dazed for 1 round instead of staggered. You can expend one use of mythic power when you hit with a Gorgon's Fist attack, but before the saving throw is attempted, to increase its DC by %1.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Gorgon's Fist.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Gorgon's Fist	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Great Fortitude (Mythic)		KEY:Great Fortitude					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Great Fortitude																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your fortitude is unmatched.																																																																																																																																																																	BENEFIT:Whenever you roll a Fortitude saving throw against a spell, spell-like ability, or supernatural ability from a non-mythic source, roll twice and take the higher result.	INFO:Prerequisite|Great Fortitude.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Great Fortitude	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Guided Hand (Mythic)			KEY:Guided Hand						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Guided Hand																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Attacks made with your deity's favored weapon are divinely inspired.																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:When making attacks with your deity's favored weapon, you can add your Wisdom modifier instead of your Strength or Dexterity modifier on damage rolls.	INFO:Prerequisite|Guided Hand.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Guided Hand	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Mythic Guided Hand Selection|1	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Heroic Defiance (Mythic)		KEY:Heroic Defiance					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Heroic Defiance																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You ignore harmful effects that would bring others down.																																																																																																																																																																		BENEFIT:Once per day as an immediate action, you can attempt to negate the onset of one harmful condition or affliction (such as panicked, paralyzed, stunned, and so on) that allowed a saving throw for its onset, not including permanent and instantaneous conditions. When you do so, attempt a Will saving throw with a +%1 bonus against the original DC of the effect. If you succeed, the condition is negated. If you fail, the onset is delayed until the end of your next turn, after which it takes its normal effect. This feat has no effect on hit point damage or ability damage.&nl;This effect is separate from the use of non-mythic Heroic Defiance.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Heroic Defiance.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Heroic Defiance	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Heroic Recovery (Mythic)		KEY:Heroic Recovery					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Heroic Recovery																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can shrug off the effects of harmful conditions after they've taken effect.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to use Heroic Recovery additional times. Whenever you do, add +%1 to the result of the Fortitude save.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Heroic Recovery.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Heroic Recovery	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Improved Bull Rush (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Bull Rush				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Bull Rush																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You push foes around with amazing ease.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_BullRush,CMD_BullRush|HalfMythicLevel																																											BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to bull rush, and to your CMD when an opponent bull rushes you. These bonuses stack with those granted by non-mythic Improved Bull Rush.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to bull rush you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Bull Rush.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Bull Rush	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Improved Channel (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Channel					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Channel																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:As a divine conduit for energy, you're unmatched.																																																																																																																																																													BENEFIT:Non-mythic creatures that take damage from your channel energy must roll their saving throws twice and take the lower result.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Channel.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Channel	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Improved Counterspell (Mythic)	KEY:Improved Counterspell				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Counterspell																										PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your innate understanding of magical mechanics allows you to unravel spells with pure magical energy.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:When counterspelling, you can use a spell of the same school that is the same or higher spell level as the target spell.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Counterspell.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Counterspell	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Improved Critical (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Critical					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Critical																								PREATT:8		PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your critical strikes with your chosen weapon are deadlier than most.																				MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|ABILITY=FEAT[Improved Critical]																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:Your critical multiplier with your chosen weapon is increased by 1 (to a maximum of x6).	INFO:Special|You can gain this feat multiple times. The effects do not stack. Each time you take this feat, it applies to a different non-mythic Improved Critical feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Critical, base attack bonus +8.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Critical	BONUS:WEAPONPROF=%LIST|CRITMULTADD|1	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Improved Dirty Trick (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Dirty Trick				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Dirty Trick																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're a paragon of down-and-dirty fighting.																																																																																																																		BONUS:VAR|CMB_DirtyTricks,CMD_DirtyTricks|HalfMythicLevel																																										BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to attempt a dirty trick, and to your CMD when an opponent attempts to perform a dirty trick on you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Dirty Trick.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts a dirty trick maneuver against you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Dirty Trick.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Dirty Trick	SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Improved Disarm (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Disarm					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Disarm																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're expert at knocking your enemies' weapons away.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_Disarm,CMD_Disarm|HalfMythicLevel																																												BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to disarm, and to your CMD when an opponent tries to disarm you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Disarm.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to disarm you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Disarm.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Disarm	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Drag (Mythic)			KEY:Improved Drag					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Drag																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You pull your enemies around the battlefield with great ease.																																																																																																																				BONUS:VAR|CMB_Drag,CMD_Drag|HalfMythicLevel																																													BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to attempt a drag combat maneuver, and to your CMD when an opponent attempts a drag combat maneuver against you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Drag.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts a drag maneuver against you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Drag.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Drag	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Familiar (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Familiar					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Familiar																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your familiar gains some of your incredible resiliency and insight.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:For every 3 tiers you possess, your familiar gains a +2 bonus to an ability score of your choice. These bonuses stack. Your familiar adds your tier to its natural armor bonus and to its spell resistance (if it has spell resistance).	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Familiar.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Familiar	DEFINE:Feat_Master_Has_MythicImprovedFamiliar|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_Master_Has_MythicImprovedFamiliar|1|TYPE=Boolean	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Grapple (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Grapple					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your wrestling moves are difficult to counter.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_Grapple,CMD_Grapple|HalfMythicLevel																																												BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to grapple, and to your CMD when an opponent tries to grapple you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Grapple.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to grapple you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Grapple.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Grapple	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Initiative (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Initiative				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Initiative																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You leap into the fray with speed and confidence.																																																			BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|MythicLevel																																																																																																																		BENEFIT:The bonus on initiative checks granted by Improved Initiative increases by %1. This bonus stacks with the bonus from Improved Initiative. In addition, instead of rolling initiative, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat your roll as a natural 20.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Initiative.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Initiative	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Overrun (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Overrun					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Overrun																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're an unstoppable force on the battlefield, able to run down lesser foes with ease.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_Overrun,CMD_Overrun|HalfMythicLevel																																												BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to overrun, and to your CMD when an opponent tries to overrun you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Overrun.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to overrun you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Overrun.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Overrun	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Reposition (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Reposition				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Reposition																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You put your foes right where you want them.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_Reposition,CMD_Reposition|HalfMythicLevel																																											BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to attempt a reposition combat maneuver, and to your CMD when an opponent attempts to perform a reposition combat maneuver against you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Reposition.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to reposition you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Reposition.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Reposition	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Steal (Mythic)			KEY:Improved Steal					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Steal																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your light fingers can lift even the most closely held item off an enemy.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_Steal,CMD_Steal|HalfMythicLevel																																												BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to attempt a steal combat maneuver, and to your CMD when an opponent attempts a steal combat maneuver on you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Steal.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts a steal maneuver against, you unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Steal.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Steal	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Stonecunning (Mythic)	KEY:Improved Stonecunning				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Stonecunning																										PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1	SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=(MythicLevel*2)|Stone Tell																									DESC:If you listen close, you can hear the secrets of stone.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:You gain stone tell as a spell-like ability usable once per day with a caster level equal to twice your tier.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Stonecunning.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Stonecunning	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Sunder (Mythic)		KEY:Improved Sunder					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Sunder																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your mighty smashing blows demolish objects.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|CMB_Sunder,CMD_Sunder|HalfMythicLevel																																												BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to sunder, and to your CMD when an opponent tries to sunder an object used by you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Sunder.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to sunder an object used by you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Sunder.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Sunder	SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Improved Trip (Mythic)			KEY:Improved Trip					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Trip																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're expert at knocking your foes down.																																																																																																																				BONUS:VAR|CMB_Trip,CMD_Trip|HalfMythicLevel																																													BENEFIT:You gain a bonus equal to half your tier on checks to trip, and to your CMD when an opponent tries to trip you. These bonuses stack with those granted by Improved Trip.&nl;Furthermore, you can make an attack of opportunity against any creature that attempts to trip you, unless it also has this feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Trip.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Trip	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Improved Unarmed Strike (Mythic)	KEY:Improved Unarmed Strike				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Unarmed Strike																										PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your unarmed strikes are more powerful than others.																																									BONUS:COMBAT|DAMAGE.Unarmed|HalfMythicLevel																																																																																																																BENEFIT:You can add %1 to your damage with unarmed strikes. As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to overcome the hardness of objects with your unarmed strikes. This effect last for %2 rounds. If an object's hardness is greater than 15, you don't ignore any of its hardness.|HalfMythicLevel|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Improved Unarmed Strike.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Improved Unarmed Strike	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Intimidating Prowess (Mythic)		KEY:Intimidating Prowess				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Intimidating Prowess																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your mythic stature makes others uneasy.																																																																																																	BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|MythicLevel																																																											BENEFIT:You gain a +%1 bonus on Intimidate checks against non-mythic creatures, or +%2 against mythic creatures. If you also have the Persuasive (mythic) feat, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat the Intimidate check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before the roll is made.|MythicLevel|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Intimidating Prowess.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Intimidating Prowess	BONUS:SITUATION|Intimidate=Mythic Creature|HalfMythicLevel-MythicLevel	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Iron Will (Mythic)			KEY:Iron Will						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Iron Will																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your will is incorruptible.																																																																																																																																																																BENEFIT:Whenever you roll a Will saving throw against a spell, spell-like ability, or supernatural ability from a non-mythic source, roll twice and take the higher result.	INFO:Prerequisite|Iron Will.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Iron Will	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Knockout Artist (Mythic)		KEY:Knockout Artist					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Knockout Artist																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your knockout punches are truly mighty.																																																																																																																																																																				BENEFIT:When you use your unarmed strike to deal nonlethal damage and sneak attack damage to an opponent, roll d8s for each sneak attack die instead of d6s.	INFO:Prerequisite|Knockout Artist.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Knockout Artist	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Lightning Reflexes (Mythic)		KEY:Lightning Reflexes				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Lightning Reflexes																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your reflexes are superhuman.																																																																																																																																																																BENEFIT:Whenever you roll a Reflex saving throw against a spell, spell-like ability, or supernatural ability from a non-mythic source, roll twice and take the higher result.	INFO:Prerequisite|Lightning Reflexes.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Lightning Reflexes	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Lucky Halfling (Mythic)			KEY:Lucky Halfling					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Lucky Halfling																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You share your mythic luck with those around you.																																																																																																																																																														BENEFIT:When you use Lucky Halfling, add +%1 as a bonus on the saving throw. You can expend one use of mythic power when an ally uses your save but still suffers an effect on a successful saving throw. If you do, that ally suffers no effect on the successful saving throw.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Lucky Halfling.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Lucky Halfling	SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Lunge (Mythic)				KEY:Lunge							CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Lunge																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your reaching strikes aid your defenses against those you hit.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:Whenever you use Lunge and hit a creature with the melee attack, you no longer take a -2 penalty to AC against that creature. You can expend one use of mythic power when you use Lunge to negate the -2 penalty to AC whether you hit or miss, and gain a +2 bonus on attacks of opportunity you make while Lunge is in effect.	INFO:Prerequisite|Lunge.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Lunge	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Magical Aptitude (Mythic)		KEY:Magical Aptitude					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Magical Aptitude																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your understanding of the principles and intricacies of magic goes far beyond your training.																																																																																							BONUS:SKILL|Spellcraft,Use Magic Device|2																																																											BENEFIT:The bonus on Spellcraft and Use Magic Device skill checks from Magical Aptitude increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat a Spellcraft or Use Magic Device check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Magical Aptitude.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Magical Aptitude	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Manyshot (Mythic)				KEY:Manyshot						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Manyshot																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can fire a barrage of arrows at your target with very little effort.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:When making a full-attack action with a bow and using Manyshot, you fire two arrows with both your first and second attacks, instead of just your first attack.	INFO:Prerequisite|Manyshot.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Manyshot	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Medusa's Wrath (Mythic)			KEY:Medusa's Wrath					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Medusa's Wrath																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your barrage of unarmed attacks builds to a single, staggering strike.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:You may forgo the two additional unarmed strikes of Medusa's Wrath to instead make a single unarmed strike at your highest base attack bonus. If you successfully hit your opponent, it must succeed at a Fortitude saving throw (DC %1) or be staggered for 1 round. You can expend one use of mythic power when you stagger a target with Medusa's Wrath to extend the duration of the staggered condition by %2 rounds.|Feat_MythicMedusasWrath_DC|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Medusa's Wrath.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Medusa's Wrath	DEFINE:Feat_MythicMedusasWrath_DC|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_MythicMedusasWrath_DC|10+floor(TL/2)+WIS	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Missile Shield (Mythic)			KEY:Missile Shield					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Missile Shield																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your remarkable awareness allows you to deflect multiple ranged attacks and even ray spells.																																																																																																																																																																				BENEFIT:When using Missile Shield, you can deflect %1 additional ranged attacks per round. You can expend one use of mythic power as an immediate action to deflect a single ray from a ray spell or effect targeting you.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Missile Shield.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Missile Shield	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Mobility (Mythic)				KEY:Mobility						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Mobility																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You have perfected your ability to weave through the battlefield, using your momentum to propel yourself far.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:Whenever you use Mobility, you gain a +6 dodge bonus to AC instead of the normal +4. In addition, once per round when an attack of opportunity provoked by your movement misses you, you may move 5 feet as a free action. This movement doesn't count against your total overall movement for the round, but it does provoke attacks of opportunity.	INFO:Prerequisite|Mobility.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Mobility	BONUS:VAR|Feat_Mobility_DodgeBonus|6|TYPE=Base	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Monastic Legacy (Mythic)		KEY:Monastic Legacy					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Monastic Legacy																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Every new experience carries you another step further along your path to enlightenment.																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:Add half the levels you have in classes other than monk to your monk level to determine your effective monk level for your AC bonus. As a free action, you can expend one use of mythic power to add half your tier to your effective monk level to determine your base unarmed strike damage and AC bonus until the start of your next turn.	INFO:Prerequisite|Monastic Legacy.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Monastic Legacy	TEMPBONUS:PC|UDAM|CLASS.Monk|HalfMythicLevel	TEMPBONUS:PC|VAR|MonkUnarmedDamageLVL|HalfMythicLevel	BONUS:VAR|MonkACLVL|(TL-MonkLVL-HD)/2	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Mounted Archery (Mythic)		KEY:Mounted Archery					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Mounted Archery																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your skill as a rider allows you to take cover and shoot with amazing accuracy.																																																																																																																																																																	BENEFIT:When using the Ride skill to use your mount as cover, you can still make a single ranged weapon attack as a standard action. While your mount is moving, you can expend one use of mythic power to negate the penalties for making ranged weapon attacks while mounted until the beginning of your next turn.	INFO:Prerequisite|Mounted Archery.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Mounted Archery	SOURCEPAGE:p.69
Mounted Combat (Mythic)			KEY:Mounted Combat					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Mounted Combat																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your ability to maneuver a mount through the rigors of combat is nearly unparalleled.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:You can negate %1 additional hits against your mount per round. Once per round as an immediate action, you can expend one use of mythic power to substitute a Ride check for a single Reflex saving throw your mount must make.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Mounted Combat.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Mounted Combat	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Mythic Crafter (Mythic)			KEY:Mythic Crafter					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=ItemCreation																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can craft mythic magic items.																																																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:You can create any mythic magic item for which you have the appropriate item creation feat. In addition, you gain a +5 bonus on skill checks when creating non-mythic magic items.	INFO:Prerequisite|Any item creation feat.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Mythic Crafter	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Natural Spell (Mythic)			KEY:Natural Spell					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Natural Spell																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can speak and use some magic items when you use wild shape.																																																																																																																																																																				BENEFIT:When you're using wild shape, you can use spell completion and spell trigger magic items that were on your person when you changed form. You don't need to physically manipulate the items when you use them while using wild shape. Furthermore, you can speak normally when using wild shape.	INFO:Prerequisite|Natural Spell.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Natural Spell	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Nimble Moves (Mythic)			KEY:Nimble Moves					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Nimble Moves																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You dance across obstacles with ease, as though they weren't even there.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:For every 2 tiers you possess, you can move through up to 5 feet of difficult terrain each round as if it were normal terrain (minimum 5 feet). This effect stacks with those provided by Nimble Moves and Acrobatic Steps.	INFO:Prerequisite|Nimble Moves.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Nimble Moves	DEFINE:Feat_NimbleMoves_Squares|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_NimbleMoves_Squares|max(5,floor(MythicLevel/2*5))	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Penetrating Strike (Mythic)		KEY:Penetrating Strike				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Penetrating Strike																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You know just how to strike to bypass even the most heavily armored foe's defenses.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:When using Penetrating Strike or Greater Penetrating Strike, you can ignore %1 additional poinst of damage reduction. Additionally, the effects apply to damage reduction without a type (such as DR 10/-).|max(1,floor(MythicLevel/3))	INFO:Prerequisite|Penetrating Strike.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Penetrating Strike	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Persuasive (Mythic)			KEY:Persuasive						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Persuasive																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're a master of persuasion, be it with soothing words or harsh barking commands.																																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy,Intimidate|2																																																												BENEFIT:The bonus on Diplomacy and Intimidate skill checks granted by Persuasive increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat a Diplomacy or Intimidate check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Persuasive.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Persuasive	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Pinpoint Targeting (Mythic)		KEY:Pinpoint Targeting				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Pinpoint Targeting																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your attacks can home in on your opponent's weak spot and ignore many defenses.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:You can use this feat even if you move this round, but only if the distance you move is equal to or less than %1 feet.|MythicLevel*5	INFO:Prerequisite|Pinpoint Targeting.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Pinpoint Targeting	SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Point-Blank Shot (Mythic)		KEY:Point-Blank Shot					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point-Blank Shot																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your accuracy with ranged attacks is unmatched at point-blank range.																																																	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT-SHORTRANGE,DAMAGE-SHORTRANGE|1																																																																																																															BENEFIT:The bonus on attack and damage rolls granted by Point-Blank Shot increases to +2. As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to gain a +%1 additional bonus on these rolls.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Point-Blank Shot.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Point-Blank Shot	SOURCEPAGE:p.71
Power Attack (Mythic)			KEY:Power Attack					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Power Attack																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your attacks are truly devastating.																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|PowerAttackDamageBase|1																																															BENEFIT:When you use Power Attack, you gain a +3 bonus on melee damage rolls instead of +2. When your base attack bonus reaches +4 and every 4 points thereafter, the amount of bonus damage increases by +3 instead of +2. In addition, the bonus damage from this feat is doubled on a critical hit, before it's multiplied by the weapon's critical multiplier.&nl;You can expend one use of mythic power when you activate Power Attack to ignore the penalties on melee attack rolls and combat maneuver checks for 1 minute.	INFO:Prerequisite|Power Attack.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Power Attack	SOURCEPAGE:p.71
Powerful Shape (Mythic)			KEY:Powerful Shape					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Powerful Shape																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:The forms you take in wild shape tower over their natural counterparts.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:You can apply the giant simple template to any form you take with wild shape. This replaces the benefit from Powerful Shape.&nl;As a free action, you can expend one use of mythic power to combine the benefit from this feat with the benefit from non-mythic Powerful Shape for a number of rounds equal to your tier.	INFO:Prerequisite|Powerful Shape.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Powerful Shape	SOURCEPAGE:p.71
Prophetic Visionary (Mythic)		KEY:Prophetic Visionary				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Prophetic Visionary																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your precognitive powers aid you further.																																																																																																																																																																												BENEFIT:You can use Prophetic Visionary's augury ability at will, spending 10 minutes in a deep trance each time. Your chance of a successful augury increases by %1%%. A successful augury made by using this feat also grants you the benefits of guidance, but the bonus is +%1 and is an insight bonus instead of a competence bonus.|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Prophetic Visionary.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Prophetic Visionary	SOURCEPAGE:p.71
Quick Draw (Mythic)			KEY:Quick Draw						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Quick Draw																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can retrieve any item quickly, not just weapons.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:You can use Quick Draw to draw items of any kind, not just weapons, provided they are stored or concealed on your person. As a move action, you can expend one use of mythic power to retrieve up to two hidden items. You must have two hands free to do so.	INFO:Prerequisite|Quick Draw.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Quick Draw	SOURCEPAGE:p.71
#Find a way to implement Racial Heritage
Racial Heritage (Mythic)		KEY:Racial Heritage					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Racial Heritage																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your racial heritage mingles with your mythic power to become more pronounced.																																																																																																																																																																								BENEFIT:You gain a single racial trait of your choice from the race you picked when you took non-mythic Racial Heritage. That racial trait can't modify your size or ability scores. You also gain the racial language of the race (if any) if you don't already know it. For races with multiple racial languages, you gain all of them.	INFO:Prerequisite|Racial Heritage.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Racial Heritage	SOURCEPAGE:p.71
Rapid Reload (Mythic)			KEY:Rapid Reload					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Rapid Reload																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can reload any type of weapon with astounding speed.																																																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:You gain the benefits of Rapid Reload with all crossbows and firearms, not just the one you originally chose when you gained that feat. As a swift action, you can expend one use of mythic power to gain the ability to reload crossbows and firearms without provoking attacks of opportunity for 1 minute.	INFO:Prerequisite|Rapid Reload.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Rapid Reload	SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Rapid Shot (Mythic)			KEY:Rapid Shot						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Rapid Shot																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can fire many times each round with amazing precision.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:When using Rapid Shot, you can either ignore the feat's -2 penalty on attack rolls or make two additional attacks instead of one.	INFO:Prerequisite|Rapid Shot.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Rapid Shot	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Rapid Shot (Mythic) ~ Ignore Penalty|Rapid Shot (Mythic) ~ Additional Attack	SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Rhetorical Flourish (Mythic)		KEY:Rhetorical Flourish				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Rhetorical Flourish																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're supremely skilled at using verbal misdirection and finesse to influence others.																																																																																																																																																																					BENEFIT:When you successfully use Rhetorical Flourish against a non-mythic creature, the bonus on your Diplomacy check increases by +%1. If the target is a mythic creature, you instead increase the bonus by +%2. You can expend one use of mythic power to reroll a single failed Bluff check. You must take the new result even if it is lower.|MythicLevel|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Rhetorical Flourish.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Rhetorical Flourish	SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Ride-By Attack (Mythic)			KEY:Ride-By Attack					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Ride-By Attack																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You can make multiple attacks as you ride past your enemies.																																																																																																																																																																				BENEFIT:When you successfully strike an opponent as part of a Ride-By Attack, you can continue to make attacks against successive targets. You can make up to %1 additional attacks, but you can't make more attacks than you could if you were making a full attack. Successive attacks use the lower bonus for multiple attacks, as when making a full attack. You must move at least 10 feet between each attack.|max(1,floor(MythicLevel/3))	INFO:Prerequisite|Ride-By Attack.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Ride-By Attack	SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Run (Mythic)				KEY:Run							CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Run																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You run with preternatural speed and endurance.																																																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:When running, you move seven times your normal speed if wearing medium, light, or no armor and carrying no more than a medium load, or six times your speed if wearing heavy armor or carrying a heavy load. When making a jump after a running start, you gain an additional +%1 bonus on your Acrobatics check. You can run normally for %2 rounds, but after that you must succeed at Constitution checks to continue running.|4+MythicLevel|CON+MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Run.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Run	SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Saving Shield (Mythic)			KEY:Saving Shield					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Saving Shield																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Shielding a comrade from harm gives you a chance to strike back.																																																																																																																																																																			BENEFIT:The shield bonus you grant an ally with Saving Shield increases to +3. If you use Saving Shield to successfully negate an attack against an adjacent ally, you can immediately make an attack of opportunity against the attacker so long as it is within your melee reach.	INFO:Prerequisite|Saving Shield.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Saving Shield	SOURCEPAGE:p.72
