Spellbreaker (Mythic)			KEY:Spellbreaker					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spellbreaker																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're a spellcaster's worst nightmare.																																																																																																																																																																		BENEFIT:Any non-mythic creature you threaten provokes an attack of opportunity from you whenever it uses a spell or spell-like ability, even when casting defensively or casting a quickened spell.&nl;If a non-mythic creature within 30 feet of you uses a spell or spell-like ability, you can expend one use of mythic power to make a ranged attack against that creature as an attack of opportunity (even if the creature wouldn't normally provoke attacks of opportunity). You must have a ranged weapon in hand or have a free hand and the non-mythic Quick Draw feat to use this ability. You can use this ability against a mythic creature by expending two uses of mythic power.	INFO:Prerequisite|Spellbreaker.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Spellbreaker	SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Spirited Charge (Mythic)		KEY:Spirited Charge					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spirited Charge																											PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your mounted charge knocks the wind and wits from those foolish enough to stand against you.																																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:When you hit an opponent with a mounted charge, that opponent must succeed at a Fortitude saving throw (DC %1) or be staggered for %2 rounds. If you use a lance with this attack, increase the saving throw DC by 2. As a free action before you make the attack, you can expend one use of mythic power to daze your opponent on a failed saving throw instead of staggering it.|Feat_SpiritedCharge_MythicDC|MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Spirited Charge.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Spirited Charge	DEFINE:Feat_SpiritedCharge_MythicDC|0	BONUS:VAR|Feat_SpiritedCharge_MythicDC|10+floor(TL/2)+STR	SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Spontaneous Metafocus (Mythic)	KEY:Spontaneous Metafocus				CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spontaneous Metafocus																										PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You apply metamagic to your spells with greater ease than do other spontaneous casters.																	STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITYSELECTION|FEAT|Spontaneous Metafocus																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:You can change which spell your Spontaneous Metafocus feat applies to each morning when you restore your expended spell slots. The spell it applies to can be of any level, but it must be a legal selection for the Spontaneous Metafocus feat.	INFO:Special|You can gain this feat multiple times. The effects do not stack. Each time you take this feat, it applies to a different non-mythic Spontaneous Metafocus feat.	INFO:Prerequisite|Spontaneous Metafocus.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Spontaneous Metafocus	SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Spring Attack (Mythic)			KEY:Spring Attack					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spring Attack																									PREATT:6		PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You move across the battlefield in a blur of whirling blades.																																																																																																																																																																									BENEFIT:When you use Spring Attack, you don't need to move at least 10 feet before making the first attack. If you expend one use of mythic power when you start a Spring Attack, the movement you make during the Spring Attack doesn't provoke attacks of opportunity.	INFO:Prerequisite|Spring Attack, base attack bonus +6.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Spring Attack	SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Stealthy (Mythic)				KEY:Stealthy						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Stealthy																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your grace and fluidity are beyond compare.																																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist,Stealth|2																																																												BENEFIT:The bonus on Escape Artist and Stealth skill checks from Stealthy increases by 2. In addition, you can expend one use of mythic power to treat an Escape Artist or Stealth check as if you had rolled a natural 20. You must decide to use this ability before making the roll.	INFO:Prerequisite|Stealthy.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Stealthy	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
Strike Back (Mythic)			KEY:Strike Back						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Strike Back																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your precise counterattacks degrade your foes' advantages in combat.																																																																																																																																																																						BENEFIT:When you make a melee attack as a readied action against a foe outside your melee reach, you can take a 5-foot step toward that foe. If you expend one use of mythic power, you can move your speed toward the foe instead. Neither of these counts toward the movement made during your turn.	INFO:Prerequisite|Strike Back.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Strike Back	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
