Throw Anything (Mythic)			KEY:Throw Anything					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Throw Anything																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You're so skilled at throwing weapons that it hardly matters what you throw.																																																																																																																																																															BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls and damage rolls made using an improvised thrown weapon or splash weapon. This bonus stacks with the bonus from the non-mythic Throw Anything feat. If you miss with a thrown splash weapon, it always lands adjacent to its target regardless of how many range increments it was thrown.	INFO:Prerequisite|Throw Anything.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Throw Anything	BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Splash|DAMAGE,TOHIT|2	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
Toughness (Mythic)			KEY:Toughness						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Toughness																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:You have legendary resilience and durability.																																																																																									BONUS:HP|CURRENTMAX|max(3,TL)|PRERULE:1,DAMAGE_HP																																																																		BENEFIT:Toughness provides you twice as many hit points. In addition, when you're below 0 hit points, you gain DR 10/epic. This DR stacks with any other DR/epic you might possess.	INFO:Prerequisite|Toughness.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Toughness	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
Trample (Mythic)				KEY:Trample						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Trample																													PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your rearing mount can stomp foes into the ground, barely breaking stride.																																																																																																																																																																							BENEFIT:Your mount can make two hoof attacks against an opponent you knock down with an overrun, instead of one. You can expend one use of mythic power when you score a critical hit with one or more of those hoof attacks. When you do, the critical is automatically confirmed. If both scored critical hits, expending one use of mythic power automatically confirms both.	INFO:Prerequisite|Trample.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Trample	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
Tripping Staff (Mythic)			KEY:Tripping Staff					CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Tripping Staff																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:Your staff is valuable for attack and defensive balance.																																																																																																																																																										BENEFIT:You add +%1 to CMD against trip maneuvers and on combat maneuver checks to trip with a quarterstaff. When you're wielding a quarterstaff and an opponent you threaten attempts to trip you and fails, it provokes an attack of opportunity from you. You must use your staff for this attack of opportunity.|HalfMythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Tripping Staff.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Tripping Staff	BONUS:VAR|CMD_Trip|HalfMythicLevel	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
Turn Undead (Mythic)			KEY:Turn Undead						CATEGORY:Mythic Feat		TYPE:Mythic	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Turn Undead																												PREVARGTEQ:MythicTierLevel,1																																				DESC:The power of your divine energy can not only cause undead to flee but also destroy them where they stand.																																																																																																																																																																		BENEFIT:When you use Turn Undead, the range increases by %1 feet, and non-mythic undead take a -%2 penalty on their saving throws.&nl;You can expend one use of mythic power when using Turn Undead to destroy undead. Instead of fleeing, undead that fail their saves might be destroyed. You destroy %3d4 Hit Dice worth of undead. Undead with the fewest HD are affected first; among undead with equal HD, those that are closest to the burst's point of origin are affected first. No undead of 9 or more HD can be affected, and HD that aren't sufficient to affect an undead are wasted.|10*MythicLevel|MythicLevel|2*MythicLevel	INFO:Prerequisite|Turn Undead.	ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Mythic Feat Output ~ Turn Undead	SOURCEPAGE:p.75
